The paper discusses techniques for improving the performance of multi-dimensional graph-based codes, which are commonly used in data storage devices. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT), as well as data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions interference and channel non-uniformity, which are common issues in wireless communication systems (cs.SI) and networked information systems (cs.NI).
